<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Thousands of Westpac customers have been left with access to funds with the bank's app and website going down on Monday. </p>

<p>The issue was acknowledge by the bank at about 10am on Monday morning.  </p>

<p>'There are currently issues with Westpac Live Online and Mobile Banking - we're working to fix these ASAP and will keep you updated here,' the company tweeted. </p>

<p> Thousands of Westpac customers have been left with access to funds after the bank's app and website crashed on Monday morning </p>

<p>Customers posted their frustrations online with many tweeted they were without money. </p>

<p>'Damn, I need to get out of the habit of only transfering as much as I need for the day to my debit card. Now I can't buy even my lunch today,' one person wrote. </p>

<p>'Yeah, no kidding. Can't access it on the iPhone, the iPad or the website and I can't remember my 3 digit access code for phone banking. All I want is to know what my bloody balance is!' another said. </p>

<p>'As if life in Victoria isn't bad enough right now. Can't even get into our bank accounts. Does it ever end,' added a third. </p>

<p>Daily Mail Australia has contacted Westpac for comment.  </p>
